<img src=http://24.116.149.140/tux.jpg height=120 width=120></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uclanmcstump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ClanMcStump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/10/02 6:41:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=805.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Planes and Guns</span><hr size=1> I didnt read the article... just responded to you saying you couldnt think of any drawbacks.<br>
<br>
Do I think crewmembers should be armed? No.  And maybe.  Flight attendants should NOT be armed.  We dont want these people engaging in a firefight with possible terrorists with the passengers caught in the crossfire.  The pilot, co-pilot, and navigator COULD be armed.  But they should be behind a secured reinforced door which is locked at all times and can only be opened from the inside.  If hijackers have no access to the pilot/flight control cabin then having the pilot etc being armed is a little redundant.  But in case hijackers DO gain access to the flight control cabin, a little redundancy couldnt hurt.<br>
<br>
Stymp McStump <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax Sceleris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/10/02 7:02:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=805.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Planes and Guns</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The key here is time and money. When possibly thousands of lives can be lost by the acts of just a few men, money shouldn't be a concern. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
